cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.AL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed graph algorithms in networks.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the communication capacity of nodes in a network.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents algorithms for various graph problems.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be a possible category as the paper studies the communication model of nodes in a network.
- cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is also relevant as the paper analyzes the complexity of distributed graph computations in a specific communication model.
